{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770141706,"nonce":"ALIjGQqgCE/e9B15onMfeq+splY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87oArhx","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/153","origin":"github"},"title":"worktree_create.sh creates inefficient layer worktrees (uses vcs import instead of git worktrees)","message":"## Problem\n\n`worktree_create.sh --type layer` currently uses `vcs import` (line 203-205) to clone fresh copies of all package repositories. This defeats the purpose of worktrees and wastes disk space and build time.\n\n## Current Behavior (WRONG)\n\nWhen creating a layer worktree for issue #123 targeting `core` layer:\n\n```bash\n./worktree_create.sh --issue 123 --type layer --layer core\n```\n\n**What happens** (lines 203-205):\n```bash\ncd \"$WORKTREE_DIR/${LAYER_WS}/src\"\nvcs import \u003c \"$REPOS_FILE\"\n```\n\nThis **clones fresh copies** of all repositories:\n```\nlayers/worktrees/issue-123/\n  ├── core_ws/\n  │   └── src/\n  ├── platforms_ws/ -\u003e ../../main/platforms_ws/\n  └── sensors_ws/ -\u003e ../../main/sensors_ws/\n```\n\n**Problems**:\n1. ❌ Wastes disk space (full clone of every repo)\n2. ❌ Wastes build time (can't reuse compiled artifacts)\n3. ❌ Defeats the purpose of git worktrees (isolation without redundancy)\n\n---\n\n## Desired Behavior\n\nLayer worktrees should use **hybrid structure** combining git worktrees and symlinks:\n\n### Design Principle\n- **Modified packages**: Create git worktrees (isolated changes, shared git history)\n- **Unmodified packages in target layer**: Symlink to main (reuse builds)\n- **Other layers**: Symlink entire layer (reuse builds)\n\n### Example Structure\n\nWorking on `unh_marine_autonomy` in core layer:\n\n```\nlayers/worktrees/issue-123/\n  ├── core_ws/                              (real directory)\n  │   └── src/\n  │       ├── unh_marine_autonomy/          (git worktree from main - MODIFIED)\n  │       ├── camp/ -\u003e ../../../../main/core_ws/src/camp/  (symlink)\n  │       └── other_pkg/ -\u003e ../../../../main/core_ws/src/other_pkg/\n  ├── platforms_ws/ -\u003e ../../main/platforms_ws/\n  └── sensors_ws/ -\u003e ../../main/sensors_ws/\n```\n\n### Benefits\n1. ✅ **Disk efficiency**: Only modified package has git worktree\n2. ✅ **Build efficiency**: Symlinked packages reuse compiled artifacts from main\n3. ✅ **Isolation**: Git worktree allows isolated changes without affecting main\n4. ✅ **Multi-package support**: Can create worktrees for multiple packages if needed (coordinated changes across packages)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Minimum Viable Fix\n\nFor single-package modification (most common case):\n\n1. **Add `--package` parameter** to specify which package to modify:\n   ```bash\n   ./worktree_create.sh --issue 123 --type layer --layer core --package unh_marine_autonomy\n   ```\n\n2. **Create git worktree for target package**:\n   ```bash\n   cd layers/main/core_ws/src/unh_marine_autonomy\n   git worktree add ../../../../../worktrees/issue-123/core_ws/src/unh_marine_autonomy\n   ```\n\n3. **Symlink all other packages** in target layer:\n   ```bash\n   for pkg in layers/main/core_ws/src/*; do\n       if [ \"$pkg\" != \"unh_marine_autonomy\" ]; then\n           ln -s ../../../../main/core_ws/src/$(basename $pkg) \\\n                 layers/worktrees/issue-123/core_ws/src/$(basename $pkg)\n       fi\n   done\n   ```\n\n4. **Symlink other layers** (already does this correctly):\n   ```bash\n   ln -s ../../main/platforms_ws layers/worktrees/issue-123/platforms_ws\n   ```\n\n### Future Enhancement\n\nFor multi-package modifications:\n\n```bash\n./worktree_create.sh --issue 123 --type layer --layer core \\\n    --packages unh_marine_autonomy,camp\n```\n\nCreate git worktrees for both packages, symlink the rest.\n\n**Use case**: Coordinated changes across multiple packages (should reference related issues for each package).\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `worktree_create.sh --type layer` creates git worktrees (not clones) for modified packages\n- [ ] Unmodified packages in target layer are symlinked to main\n- [ ] Other layers remain symlinked (existing behavior preserved)\n- [ ] `--package` parameter added to specify target package(s)\n- [ ] Documentation updated in `worktree_create.sh` header comments\n- [ ] `.agent/WORKTREE_GUIDE.md` updated to explain hybrid structure\n- [ ] Existing layer worktrees can be manually migrated (provide migration script?)\n\n---\n\n## Related\n\n- PR #143 - Documents workspace worktree structure (different from layer worktrees)\n- `.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh` lines 203-205 (current `vcs import` usage)\n\n---\n\n**Priority**: Medium - Current approach works but wastes resources\n\n**Effort**: Medium (3-4 hours) - Requires careful handling of git worktree creation for each package\n\n---\n**🤖 Reported-By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null}]}